Age_Initialization_Distribution_Type.description: Method for initializing the age distribution in the simulated population. Possible values are: DISTRIBUTION_OFF - All individuals default to age 20-years-old. DISTRIBUTION_SIMPLE - Individual ages are drawn from a distribution whose functional form and parameters are specified in the 'IndividualAttributes' demographics input layers: 'AgeDistributionFlag', 'AgeDistribution1', and 'AgeDistribution2'. DISTRIBUTION_COMPLEX - Individual ages are drawn from a piecewise linear distribution specified in the 'IndividualAttributes' demographics input layer 'AgeDistribution'.

Migration_Model.description: Model to use for migration. Possible values are: NO_MIGRATION, FIXED_RATE_MIGRATION, VARIABLE_RATE_MIGRATION and  LEVY_FLIGHTS.  Note: VARIABLE_RATE_MIGRATION and LEVY FLIGHTS are currently not supported.

Population_Scale_Type.description: Either use the initial population specified in the demographics input file or a fixed scaling of this value based on the population scaling factor parameter. Possible values are: USE_INPUT_FILE and FIXED_SCALING.

Simulation_Type.description: Type of disease being simulated. Possible values are: GENERIC_SIM, VECTOR_SIM, MALARIA_SIM, ENVIRONMENTAL_SIM, AIRBORNE_SIM, TB_SIM, STI_SIM and HIV_SIM.

Death_Rate_Dependence.description: This parameter determines how the death rate specified in the demographics file is used. Possible values are: NONDISEASE_MORTALITY_OFF, NONDISEASE_MORTALITY_BY_AGE_AND_GENDER and NONDISEASE_MORTALITY_BY_YEAR_AND_AGE_FOR_EACH_GENDER.

Susceptibility_Scale_Type.description: Alter infectivity by time or season. Possible values are: CONSTANT_SUSCEPTIBILITY, LOG_LINEAR_FUNCTION_OF_TIME

Simulation_Duration.description: Elapsed time noted in days from the start to the end of a simulation.

Simulation_Timestep.description: Value indicating simulation time step in days.

Start_Time.description: Time noted in days when the simulation begins. Enable_Disease_Mortality.description: Set to 1 to enable disease mortality. Set to 0 to disable disease mortality.

Node_Grid_Size.description: Spatial resolution indicating the node grid size for a simulation in degrees.

Enable_Heterogeneous_Intranode_Transmiss.description: Set to 1 to enable heterogeneous intra-node disease transmission. Requires individual property definitions and beta matrix to be specified. Set to 0 to disable.

Enable_Interventions.description: Set to 1 to load campaign interventions from file. Set to 0 to run a baseline simulation without campaigns.

VECTOR_SUGAR_FEEDING_ON_EMERGENCE_ONLY - Sugar feeding once at emergence. VECTOR_SUGAR_FEEDING_EVERY_FEED - Sugar feeding occurs once per blood meal. Vector_Larval_Rainfall_Mortality.description: Type of vector larval mortality function due to rainfall.  Possible values are NONE, SIGMOID, where the mortality rate grows linearly from 0 at the threshold to 1 at twice the threshold value, and SIGMOID_HABITAT_SHIFTING, where the threshold value is reduced by a factor proportional to how full the larval habitat is.

Larval_Density_Mortality_Scalar.description: A scale factor in the formula determining the larval-age-dependent mortality for the GRADUAL_INSTAR_SPECIFIC and LARVAL_AGE_DENSITY_DEPENDENT_MORTALITY_ONLY models.

Larval_Density_Mortality_Offset.description: An offset factor in the formula determining the larval-age-dependent mortality for the GRADUAL_INSTAR_SPECIFIC and LARVAL_AGE_DENSITY_DEPENDENT_MORTALITY_ONLY models.

HEG_Fecundity_Limiting.description: The fractional reduction in the number of eggs laid by a female mosquito who is homozygous in the homing endonuclease gene (HEG).

Mean_Egg_Hatch_Delay.description: Mean delay in egg hatch time noted in days from the time of oviposition.

Wolbachia_Mortality_Modification.description: The change in vector mortality due to a Wolbachia infection.

Wolbachia_Infection_Modification.description: The change in vector susceptibility to infection due to a Wolbachia infection.

Larval_Rainfall_Mortality_Threshold.description: The threshold value on daily rainfall in millimeters, above which larval mortality is applied when Vector_Larval_Rainfall_Mortality is set to either SIGMOID or SIGMOID_HABITAT_SHIFTING.

Human_Feeding_Mortality.description: Fraction (dimensionless) of mosquitoes that die while feeding on a human. As of version 1.5, this is now a one-value-per-simulation quantity.

Temporary_Habitat_Decay_Factor.description: Factor to convert raw evaporation rate (ignoring boundary layer effects) to the daily rate of larval habitat loss for temporary habitats with Habitat_Type parameter of TEMPORARY_RAINFALL.  Units are (larval carrying capacity per day) / (kg per square meter per second).

Semipermanent_Habitat_Decay_Rate.description: Daily rate of larval habitat loss for semi-permanent habitats with Habitat_Type parameter of WATER_VEGETATION or BRACKISH_SWAMP.

Rainfall_In_mm_To_Fill_Swamp.description: Millimeters of rain to fill larval habitat to capacity. Only used for vector species with Habitat_Type set to BRACKISH_SWAMP.

x_Temporary_Larval_Habitat.description: Scales the habitat size for all mosquito populations.

Vector_Species_Names.description: An array of vector species names for all species that are present in the simulation. For example, ['arabiensis', 'funestus', 'gambiae']

Listed_Events.description: The list of valid, user-defined events that will be included in the campaign. Any event used in the campaign must either be one of the built-in events or in this list.

Larval_Habitat_Types.description: An array of scaling factors used to determine the volume of habitat needed for larvae to breed. Represents the number of larvae in a 1x1-degree area. The factor multiplicatively scales the resulting weather or population dependent functional form.

Aquatic_Arrhenius_1.description: The duration of aquatic development is a decreasing function of temperature.  The daily rate of fractional progression from egg-hatching to emergence is parameterized by the Arrhenius equation, a1 * exp( -a2 / T ), with T in degrees Kelvin.  This parameter, a1, is a temperature-independent scale factor on the development rate.  Reference: Craig M.H., Snow R.W., et al. (1999). A climate-based distribution model of malaria transmission in sub-Saharan Africa. Parasitology Today 15(3) 105-111.

Aquatic_Arrhenius_2.description: The duration of aquatic development is a decreasing function of temperature.  The daily rate of fractional progression from egg-hatching to emergence is parameterized by the Arrhenius equation, a1 * exp( -a2 / T ), with T in degrees Kelvin.   This parameter, a2, governs how quickly the rate changes with temperature. Reference: Craig M.H., Snow R.W., et al. (1999). A climate-based distribution model of malaria transmission in sub-Saharan Africa. Parasitology Today 15(3) 105-111.

Infected_Arrhenius_1.description: The duration of sporogony is a decreasing function of temperature.  The daily rate of fractional progression of infected mosquitoes to an infectious state is parameterized by the Arrhenius equation, a1 * exp( -a2 / T ), with T in degrees Kelvin.   This parameter, a1, is a temperature-independent scale factor on the development rate.  Reference: Craig M.H., Snow R.W., et al. (1999). A climate-based distribution model of malaria transmission in sub-Saharan Africa. Parasitology Today 15(3) 105-111.

Infected_Arrhenius_2.description: The duration of sporogony is a decreasing function of temperature.  The daily rate of fractional progression of infected mosquitoes to an infectious state is parameterized by the Arrhenius equation, a1 * exp( -a2 / T ), with T in degrees Kelvin.   This parameter, a2, governs how quickly the rate changes with temperature.   Reference: Craig M.H., Snow R.W., et al. (1999). A climate-based distribution model of malaria transmission in sub-Saharan Africa. Parasitology Today 15(3) 105-111.

Immature_Duration.description: Factor (in days) used to calculate the rate at which immature organisms develop into adult mosquitoes, which equals 1 / (value of this parameter). Note that development from immature individual to adult is not dependent on temperature.

Days_Between_Feeds.description: Factor (in days) used to calculate the rate at which female mosquitoes attempt to feed. The rate equals 1 / (value of this parameter). The Days_Between_Feeds parameter represents a 3-day feeding cycle at normal tropical temperatures (30 C). If it is colder, the cycle is 4 days at 24 C, and if the temperature is warmer, the cycle is shorter, increasing the fraction of 2-day cycles from 30 C to 48 C. Whole temperature-dependent distribution can be shifted by changing Days_Between_Feeds which is always the value at 30 C. See Enable_Temperature_Dependent_Feeding_Cycle for weather-dependent feeding.

Anthropophily.description: Propensity (dimensionless) of the mosquito to feed on humans instead of animals, measured as a fraction of blood meals from human hosts. This propensity is important in differentiating the mosquito species.

Egg_Batch_Size.description: Size of egg batch laid by one female mosquito that has fed successfully.

Infected_Egg_Batch_Factor.description: Factor (dimensionless) used to modify egg batch size to account for effects of infection in a female mosquito. Female mosquitoes undergoing sporogony have reduced fertility.

Aquatic_Mortality_Rate.description: Base aquatic mortality per day for the species before adjustment for effects of overpopulation and drying. The rate is locally adjusted for other considerations, including overpopulation and drying out of the aquatic habitat.

Adult_Life_Expectancy.description: Number of days an average mosquito survives. The daily adult mortality rate is 1 / (value of this parameter).

Transmission_Rate.description: Probability of success of an infectious bite on an immunologically naive and uninfected individual, or the modifier of the probability of success for an individual with pre-erythrocytic immunity.

Acquire_Modifier.description: Modifier of the probability of successful infection of a mosquito by a malaria-infected individual, given the individual's infectiousness.

Infectious_Human_Feed_Mortality_Factor.description: Correction factor (dimensionless) used to modify the death rate of mosquitoes when feeding on humans, to account for the increase caused by infections in mosquitoes. Infected mosquitoes have a higher mortality rate while feeding on humans than uninfected mosquitoes.  References: Wekesa J. W., Copeland R. S. , et al. (1992). Effect of Plasmodium Falciparum on Blood Feeding Behavior of Naturally Infected Anopheles Mosquitoes in Western Kenya. Am J Trop Med Hyg 47(4): 484-488.Anderson R. A., Knols B. G. J., et al. (2000). Plasmodium falciparum sporozoites increase feeding-associated mortality of their mosquito hosts Anopheles gambiae s.l. Parasitology 120(04): 329-333.

Indoor_Feeding_Fraction.description: Fraction (dimensionless) of feeds on humans that occur indoors. Thus the fraction of feeds on humans that occur outdoors equals 1 - (value of this parameter).

Rainfall_In_mm_To_Fill_Swamp.description: Millimeters of rain to fill larval habitat to capacity. Only used for vector species with Habitat_Type set to BRACKISH_SWAMP.

x_Temporary_Larval_Habitat.description: Scales the habitat size for all mosquito populations.

Vector_Species_Names.description: An array of vector species names for all species that are present in the simulation. For example, ['arabiensis', 'funestus', 'gambiae']

Listed_Events.description: The list of valid, user-defined events that will be included in the campaign. Any event used in the campaign must either be one of the built-in events or in this list.

Larval_Habitat_Types.description: An array of scaling factors used to determine the volume of habitat needed for larvae to breed. Represents the number of larvae in a 1x1-degree area. The factor multiplicatively scales the resulting weather or population dependent functional form.

Aquatic_Arrhenius_1.description: The duration of aquatic development is a decreasing function of temperature.  The daily rate of fractional progression from egg-hatching to emergence is parameterized by the Arrhenius equation, a1 * exp( -a2 / T ), with T in degrees Kelvin.  This parameter, a1, is a temperature-independent scale factor on the development rate.  Reference: Craig M.H., Snow R.W., et al. (1999). A climate-based distribution model of malaria transmission in sub-Saharan Africa. Parasitology Today 15(3) 105-111.

Aquatic_Arrhenius_2.description: The duration of aquatic development is a decreasing function of temperature.  The daily rate of fractional progression from egg-hatching to emergence is parameterized by the Arrhenius equation, a1 * exp( -a2 / T ), with T in degrees Kelvin.   This parameter, a2, governs how quickly the rate changes with temperature. Reference: Craig M.H., Snow R.W., et al. (1999). A climate-based distribution model of malaria transmission in sub-Saharan Africa. Parasitology Today 15(3) 105-111.

Infected_Arrhenius_1.description: The duration of sporogony is a decreasing function of temperature.  The daily rate of fractional progression of infected mosquitoes to an infectious state is parameterized by the Arrhenius equation, a1 * exp( -a2 / T ), with T in degrees Kelvin.   This parameter, a1, is a temperature-independent scale factor on the development rate.  Reference: Craig M.H., Snow R.W., et al. (1999). A climate-based distribution model of malaria transmission in sub-Saharan Africa. Parasitology Today 15(3) 105-111.

Infected_Arrhenius_2.description: The duration of sporogony is a decreasing function of temperature.  The daily rate of fractional progression of infected mosquitoes to an infectious state is parameterized by the Arrhenius equation, a1 * exp( -a2 / T ), with T in degrees Kelvin.   This parameter, a2, governs how quickly the rate changes with temperature.   Reference: Craig M.H., Snow R.W., et al. (1999). A climate-based distribution model of malaria transmission in sub-Saharan Africa. Parasitology Today 15(3) 105-111.

Immature_Duration.description: Factor (in days) used to calculate the rate at which immature organisms develop into adult mosquitoes, which equals 1 / (value of this parameter). Note that development from immature individual to adult is not dependent on temperature.

Days_Between_Feeds.description: Factor (in days) used to calculate the rate at which female mosquitoes attempt to feed. The rate equals 1 / (value of this parameter). The Days_Between_Feeds parameter represents a 3-day feeding cycle at normal tropical temperatures (30 C). If it is colder, the cycle is 4 days at 24 C, and if the temperature is warmer, the cycle is shorter, increasing the fraction of 2-day cycles from 30 C to 48 C. Whole temperature-dependent distribution can be shifted by changing Days_Between_Feeds which is always the value at 30 C. See Enable_Temperature_Dependent_Feeding_Cycle for weather-dependent feeding.

Anthropophily.description: Propensity (dimensionless) of the mosquito to feed on humans instead of animals, measured as a fraction of blood meals from human hosts. This propensity is important in differentiating the mosquito species.

Egg_Batch_Size.description: Size of egg batch laid by one female mosquito that has fed successfully.

Infected_Egg_Batch_Factor.description: Factor (dimensionless) used to modify egg batch size to account for effects of infection in a female mosquito. Female mosquitoes undergoing sporogony have reduced fertility.

Aquatic_Mortality_Rate.description: Base aquatic mortality per day for the species before adjustment for effects of overpopulation and drying. The rate is locally adjusted for other considerations, including overpopulation and drying out of the aquatic habitat.

Adult_Life_Expectancy.description: Number of days an average mosquito survives. The daily adult mortality rate is 1 / (value of this parameter).

Transmission_Rate.description: Probability of success of an infectious bite on an immunologically naive and uninfected individual, or the modifier of the probability of success for an individual with pre-erythrocytic immunity.

Acquire_Modifier.description: Modifier of the probability of successful infection of a mosquito by a malaria-infected individual, given the individual's infectiousness.

Infectious_Human_Feed_Mortality_Factor.description: Correction factor (dimensionless) used to modify the death rate of mosquitoes when feeding on humans, to account for the increase caused by infections in mosquitoes. Infected mosquitoes have a higher mortality rate while feeding on humans than uninfected mosquitoes.  References: Wekesa J. W., Copeland R. S. , et al. (1992). Effect of Plasmodium Falciparum on Blood Feeding Behavior of Naturally Infected Anopheles Mosquitoes in Western Kenya. Am J Trop Med Hyg 47(4): 484-488.Anderson R. A., Knols B. G. J., et al. (2000). Plasmodium falciparum sporozoites increase feeding-associated mortality of their mosquito hosts Anopheles gambiae s.l. Parasitology 120(04): 329-333.

Indoor_Feeding_Fraction.description: Fraction (dimensionless) of feeds on humans that occur indoors. Thus the fraction of feeds on humans that occur outdoors equals 1 - (value of this parameter).

Max_Drug_IRBC_Kill.description: Maximum log reduction in IRBCs per day.

Drug_Hepatocyte_Killrate.description: Log reduction in hepatocytes per day.

Drug_Gametocyte02_Killrate.description: Log reduction per day in early-stage gametocytes.

Drug_Gametocyte34_Killrate.description: Log reduction per day in late-stage gametocytes.

Drug_GametocyteM_Killrate.description: Log reduction per day in mature gametocytes at saturated drug concentration.

Drug_PKPD_C50.description: Concentration at which drug killing rates are half of maximum. Note: This parameter and the Drug_Cmax parameter must use the same units.

Drug_Decay_T1.description: Primary drug decay rate, in days.

Drug_Decay_T2.description: Secondary drug decay rate, in days.

Drug_Fulltreatment_Doses.description: Number of doses for a full treatment.

Bodyweight_Exponent.description: Effect of body weight on maximum drug concentration in an individual patient.

Upper_Age_In_Years.description: The age (in years) below which children are given the corresponding fraction of an adult drug dose.

Fraction_Of_Adult_Dose.description: The fraction of an adult drug dose given to children below the corresponding age (in years).

Fractional_Dose_By_Upper_Age.description: An array of doses that contain Upper_Age_In_Years and Fraction_Of_Adult_Dose values.

Population_Scale_Type.description: Either use the initial population specified in the demographics input file or a fixed scaling of this value based on the population scaling factor parameter. Possible values are: USE_INPUT_FILE and FIXED_SCALING.

Simulation_Type.description: Type of disease being simulated. Possible values are: GENERIC_SIM, VECTOR_SIM, MALARIA_SIM, ENVIRONMENTAL_SIM, AIRBORNE_SIM, TB_SIM, STI_SIM and HIV_SIM.

Death_Rate_Dependence.description: This parameter determines how the death rate specified in the demographics file is used. Possible values are: NONDISEASE_MORTALITY_OFF, NONDISEASE_MORTALITY_BY_AGE_AND_GENDER and NONDISEASE_MORTALITY_BY_YEAR_AND_AGE_FOR_EACH_GENDER.

Susceptibility_Scale_Type.description: Alter infectivity by time or season. Possible values are: CONSTANT_SUSCEPTIBILITY, LOG_LINEAR_FUNCTION_OF_TIME

Simulation_Duration.description: Elapsed time noted in days from the start to the end of a simulation.

Simulation_Timestep.description: Value indicating simulation time step in days.

Start_Time.description: Time noted in days when the simulation begins. This time influences the point in the temporal input data, such as where in the climate input the DTK starts running the simulation. Note: The Start_Day of campaign events is in absolute time. So, time relative to the beginning of the simulation depends on this parameter.

Enable_Demographics_Initial.description: Uses demographics input files to configure the initial population. Enter 0 to use a standard testing sandbox which is useful for testing and validating code pathways.

Default_Geography_Torus_Size.description: TBD - When using the default geography (i.e. Enable_Demographis_Initial = 0), this is square root of the number of nodes in the simulation.  For migration, the nodes are assumed to be a torus.

Default_Geography_Initial_Node_Populatio.description: TBD - When using the default geography (i.e. Enable_Demographis_Initial = 0), this is the initial number of individuals in each node.

Enable_Vital_Dynamics.description: Set to 1 as a master switch to enable vital dynamics (births and deaths). Set to 0 to disable vital dynamics. Even when set to 1, the individual toggles for births and deaths can still disable these.

Enable_Disease_Mortality.description: Set to 1 to enable disease mortality. Set to 0 to disable disease mortality.

Node_Grid_Size.description: Spatial resolution indicating the node grid size for a simulation in degrees.

Enable_Heterogeneous_Intranode_Transmiss.description: Set to 1 to enable heterogeneous intra-node disease transmission. Requires individual property definitions and beta matrix to be specified. Set to 0 to disable.

Enable_Interventions.description: Set to 1 to load campaign interventions from file. Set to 0 to run a baseline simulation without campaigns.

Number_Basestrains.description: The number of base strains in the simulation, such as antigenic variants.

Number_Substrains.description: The number of disease substrains for each base strain, such as genetic variants.

Maternal_Transmission_Probability.description: Probability of transmission of infection from mother to infant at birth. Relevant only if Enable_Maternal_Transmission is set to 1. Note: This parameter should be set to 0 and ignored for malaria and vector simulations.

Immunity_Initialization_Distribution_Typ.description: Method for initializing the immunity distribution in the simulated population. Possible values are: DISTRIBUTION_OFF - All individuals default to no immunity. DISTRIBUTION_SIMPLE - Individual immunities are drawn from a distribution whose functional form and parameters are specified in the 'IndividualAttributes' demographics input layers: 'ImmunityDistributionFlag', 'ImmunityDistribution1', and 'ImmunityDistribution2'. DISTRIBUTION_COMPLEX - Individual immnunities are drawn from an age-dependent piecewise linear distribution specified in the 'IndividualAttributes' demographics input layer 'ImmunityDistribution'.

Listed_Events.description: The list of valid, user-defined events that will be included in the campaign. Any event used in the campaign must either be one of the built-in events or in this list.

Air_Temperature_Offset.description: The linear shift of air temperature in degrees Celsius. This is only used or needed when Climate_Model is set to CLIMATE_BY_DATA.

Land_Temperature_Offset.description: The linear shift of land surface temperature in degrees Celsius. This is only used or needed when Climate_Model is set to CLIMATE_BY_DATA.

Rainfall_Scale_Factor.description: The scalar used in multiplying rainfall value(s). This is only used or needed when Climate_Model is set to CLIMATE_BY_DATA.

Relative_Humidity_Scale_Factor.description: The scalar used in multiplying relative humidity value(s). This is only used or needed when Climate_Model is set to CLIMATE_BY_DATA.

Enable_Climate_Stochasticity.description: Controls overall stochasticity for climate. Use value 0 to disable all additional climate stochasticity. Use value 1 to enable additional variation as specified by the parameters: Air_Temperature_Variance, Land_Temperature_Variance, Enable_Rainfall_Stochasticity and Relative_Humidity_Variance.

Air_Temperature_Variance.description: The standard deviation (in degrees Celsius) for normally distributed noise applied to the daily air temperature values when Climate_Model is configured as CLIMATE_CONSTANT or CLIMATE_BY_DATA.  Only used if the Enable_Climate_Stochasticity is set to 1.

Land_Temperature_Variance.description: The standard deviation (in degrees Celsius) for normally distributed noise applied to the daily land temperature values when Climate_Model is configured as CLIMATE_CONSTANT or CLIMATE_BY_DATA.  Only used if the Enable_Climate_Stochasticity is set to 1.

Enable_Rainfall_Stochasticity.description: Set to 0 to disable rainfall stochasticity.  Set to 1 to enable stochastic variation of rainfall drawn from an exponential distribution (with a mean value as the daily rainfall from the Climate_Model values, CLIMATE_CONSTANT or CLIMATE_BY_DATA).

Relative_Humidity_Variance.description: The standard deviation (in percentage, %) for normally distributed noise applied to the daily relative humidity values when Climate_Model is configured as CLIMATE_CONSTANT or CLIMATE_BY_DATA.  Only used if the Enable_Climate_Stochasticity is set to 1.

Base_Air_Temperature.description: The value of air temperature where Climate_Model is set to CLIMATE_CONSTANT.

Base_Land_Temperature.description: The value of land temperature where Climate_Model is set to CLIMATE_CONSTANT.

Base_Rainfall.description: The value of rainfall per day in mm when Climate_Model is set to CLIMATE_CONSTANT.

Base_Relative_Humidity.description: The value of humidity where Climate_Model is set to CLIMATE_CONSTANT.

Enable_Climate_Stochasticity.description: Controls overall stochasticity for climate. Use value 0 to disable all additional climate stochasticity. Use value 1 to enable additional variation as specified by the parameters: Air_Temperature_Variance, Land_Temperature_Variance, Enable_Rainfall_Stochasticity and Relative_Humidity_Variance.

Air_Temperature_Variance.description: The standard deviation (in degrees Celsius) for normally distributed noise applied to the daily air temperature values when Climate_Model is configured as CLIMATE_CONSTANT or CLIMATE_BY_DATA.  Only used if the Enable_Climate_Stochasticity is set to 1.

Land_Temperature_Variance.description: The standard deviation (in degrees Celsius) for normally distributed noise applied to the daily land temperature values when Climate_Model is configured as CLIMATE_CONSTANT or CLIMATE_BY_DATA.  Only used if the Enable_Climate_Stochasticity is set to 1.

Enable_Rainfall_Stochasticity.description: Set to 0 to disable rainfall stochasticity.  Set to 1 to enable stochastic variation of rainfall drawn from an exponential distribution (with a mean value as the daily rainfall from the Climate_Model values, CLIMATE_CONSTANT or CLIMATE_BY_DATA).

Relative_Humidity_Variance.description: The standard deviation (in percentage, %) for normally distributed noise applied to the daily relative humidity values when Climate_Model is configured as CLIMATE_CONSTANT or CLIMATE_BY_DATA.  Only used if the Enable_Climate_Stochasticity is set to 1.

Climate_Model.description: Determines how the climate of a simulation is configured and from what file(s). Possible values are: CLIMATE_OFF, CLIMATE_CONSTANT - Uses the conditional parameters that give the fixed values of temperature or rain for land temperature, air temperature, rainfall and humidity. CLIMATE_KOPPEN - Uses an input file that decodes Koppen codes by geographic location. CLIMATE_BY_DATA - Reads everything out of several input files with additional parameters that allow the addition of stochasticity or scale offsets.

Climate_Update_Resolution.description: Update resolution for data in climate files. Possible values are: CLIMATE_UPDATE_YEAR, CLIMATE_UPDATE_MONTH, CLIMATE_UPDATE_WEEK, CLIMATE_UPDATE_DAY and CLIMATE_UPDATE_HOUR.

Air_Temperature_Filename.description: Path of input file defining air temperature data measured 2 meters above ground. Relevant only if Climate_Model is set to CLIMATE_BY_DATA.

Land_Temperature_Filename.description: Path of input file defining temperature data measured at land surface. Relevant only if Climate_Model is set to CLIMATE_BY_DATA.

Rainfall_Filename.description: Path of input file defining rainfall data. Relevant only if Climate_Model is set to CLIMATE_BY_DATA.

Relative_Humidity_Filename.description: Path of input file defining relative humidity data measured 2 meters above ground. Relevant only if Climate_Model is set to CLIMATE_BY_DATA.

Koppen_Filename.description: Path to input file used to specify Koppen climate classifications. This is only used or needed when Climate_Model is set to CLIMATE_KOPPEN.

Enable_Climate_Stochasticity.description: Controls overall stochasticity for climate. Use value 0 to disable all additional climate stochasticity. Use value 1 to enable additional variation as specified by the parameters: Air_Temperature_Variance, Land_Temperature_Variance, Enable_Rainfall_Stochasticity and Relative_Humidity_Variance.

Air_Temperature_Variance.description: The standard deviation (in degrees Celsius) for normally distributed noise applied to the daily air temperature values when Climate_Model is configured as CLIMATE_CONSTANT or CLIMATE_BY_DATA.  Only used if the Enable_Climate_Stochasticity is set to 1.

Land_Temperature_Variance.description: The standard deviation (in degrees Celsius) for normally distributed noise applied to the daily land temperature values when Climate_Model is configured as CLIMATE_CONSTANT or CLIMATE_BY_DATA.  Only used if the Enable_Climate_Stochasticity is set to 1.

Enable_Rainfall_Stochasticity.description: Set to 0 to disable rainfall stochasticity.  Set to 1 to enable stochastic variation of rainfall drawn from an exponential distribution (with a mean value as the daily rainfall from the Climate_Model values, CLIMATE_CONSTANT or CLIMATE_BY_DATA).

Relative_Humidity_Variance.description: The standard deviation (in percentage, %) for normally distributed noise applied to the daily relative humidity values when Climate_Model is configured as CLIMATE_CONSTANT or CLIMATE_BY_DATA.  Only used if the Enable_Climate_Stochasticity is set to 1.

HIV_Child_Survival_Rapid_Progressor_Rate.description: The exponential decay rate, in years, describing the distribution of HIV survival for children who are rapid progressors.

HIV_Child_Survival_Slow_Progressor_Shape.description: The Weibull shape parameter describing the distribution of HIV survival for children who are slower progressors.

HIV_Child_Survival_Slow_Progressor_Scale.description: The Weibull scale parameter describing the distribution of HIV survival for children who are slower progressors.

HIV_Child_Survival_Rapid_Progressor_Frac.description: Determines time since infection, in months, over which the Acute_Stage_Infectivity_Multiplier is applied to coital acts occurring in that time period.

HIV_Age_Max_for_Child_Survival_Function.description: Individuals infected at ages younger than HIV_Age_Max_for_Child_Survival_Function use the child survival function. Older individuals use the adult age-dependent survival function. When this parameter is set above zero and below the age of sexual debut, model results are not sensitive to this parameter value because there is no mechanism for children to become infected between infancy and sexual debut.

HIV_Age_Max_for_Adult_Age_Dependent_Surv.description: Extrapolation of this linear decline to high values of age can lead to negative values of lambda, which are not valid. To avoid negative lambda values, a maximum age is set using the parameter HIV_Age_Max_for_Age_Dependent_Survival. All individuals infected at ages greater than HIV_Age_Max_for_Age_Dependent_Survival use the survival distribution corresponding to the age set by HIV_Age_Max_for_Age_Dependent_Survival. HIV incidence in many scenarios will be relatively low in these age groups, so model results are usually not highly sensitive to this parameter value.

HIV_Adult_Survival_Scale_Parameter_Slope.description: At the time of infection, survival time is drawn from a Weibull distribution with a scale parameter that can vary linearly with age as follows: HIV_Adult_Survival_Lambda_Intercept + HIV_Adult_Survival_Lambda_Slope*Age (in years). Because survival with HIV becomes shorter with increasing age, this parameter is normally set to a negative number.

HIV_Adult_Survival_Scale_Parameter_Inter.description: At the time of infection, survival time is drawn from a Weibull distribution with a scale parameter that can vary linearly with age as follows: HIV_Adult_Survival_Lambda_Intercept + HIV_Adult_Survival_Lambda_Slope*Age (in years). This parameter sets the y-intercept of the line.

HIV_Adult_Survival_Shape_Parameter.description: At the time of infection, survival time is drawn from a Weibull distribution with this scale parameter.

Acute_Duration_In_Months.description: Determines time since infection, in months, over which the Acute_Stage_Infectivity_Multiplier is applied to coital acts occurring in that time period.

AIDS_Duration_In_Months.description: Determines the time period prior to an AIDS-related death over which the AIDS_Stage_Infectivity_Multiplier is applied.

Acute_Stage_Infectivity_Multiplier.description: Multiplier acting on Base_Infectivity to determine the per-act transmission probability of a HIV+ individual during the acute stage.

AIDS_Stage_Infectivity_Multiplier.description: Multiplier acting on Base_Infectivity to determine the per-act transmission probability of a HIV+ individual during the AIDS stage.

ART_Viral_Suppression_Multiplier.description: Multiplier acting on Base_Infectivity to determine the per-act transmission probability of a virally suppressed HIV+ individual.

Heterogeneous_Infectiousness_Weibull_Het.description: Inverse shape parameter of a Weibull distribution that governs an infectiousness multiplier. The multiplier represents heterogeneity in infectivity, and adjusts Base_Infectivity.

Heterogeneous_Infectiousness_Weibull_Sca.description: Scale parameter of a Weibull distribution that governs an infectiousness multiplier. The multiplier represents heterogeneity in infectivity, and adjusts Base_Infectivity.

ART_CD4_at_Initiation_Saturating_Reducti.description: The duration from ART enrollment to on-ART HIV-cause death increases with CD4 at ART initiation up to a threshold determined by this parameter value.

CD4_Post_Infection_Weibull_Scale.description: Scale parameter of a Weibull distribution that represents the post-acute-infection CD4 cell count.

CD4_Post_Infection_Weibull_Heterogeneity.description: Inverse shape parameter of a Weibull distribution that represents the post-acute-infection CD4 cell count.

CD4_At_Death_LogLogistic_Scale.description: Scale parameter of a Weibull distribution that represents the at-death CD4 cell count.

CD4_At_Death_LogLogistic_Heterogeneity.description: Inverse shape parameter of a Weibull distribution that represents the at-death CD4 cell count.

Report_Event_Recorder_Ignore_Events_In_L.description: If this flag is set to true, all events listed in Report_Event_Recorder_Events will be ignored. If it is set to false, all events will be recorded.

Report_Event_Recorder_Events.description: The list of events to include or exclude in the ReportEventRecorder.csv output file. This is available for both STI_SIM and HIV_SIM, but HIV_SIM simulations will have additional columns.

Report_Event_Recorder_Individual_Propert.description: Fraction of individuals in the target demographic that will receive this intervention.

Enable_Aging.description: Set to 1 to account for aging in the population. Set to 0 to assume that the population does not age.

Infection_Updates_Per_Timestep.description: Number of infection updates executed during each timestep. A timestep defaults to one day.

Enable_Immunity.description: Set to 1 if an individual has protective immunity after an infection clears. Set to 0 if recovery from the infection does not affect the individual's future immunity.

Max_Individual_Infections.description: Limit on the number of infections that an individual can have simultaneously. Note: Relevant only if the Enable_Superinfection parameter is set to 1 to allow multiple infections.

Enable_Superinfection.description: Set to 1 if an individual can have multiple infections with the same agent simultaneously. Set to 0 if multiple infections are not possible. See the Max_Individual_Infections parameter.

x_Other_Mortality.description: Multiplier for scaling mortality from causes other than disease being simulated.

Migration_Model.description: Model to use for migration. Possible values are: NO_MIGRATION, FIXED_RATE_MIGRATION, VARIABLE_RATE_MIGRATION and  LEVY_FLIGHTS.  Note: VARIABLE_RATE_MIGRATION and LEVY FLIGHTS are currently not supported.

Migration_Pattern.description: The type of roundtrip. For example, a single roundtrip. Possible values are: RANDOM_WALK_DIFFUSION, SINGLE_ROUND_TRIPS and WAYPOINTS_HOME.

Local_Migration_Roundtrip_Probability.description: Likelihood that an individual who walks into a neighboring cell will return to the cell of origin during the next migration. Relevant only when Enable_Local_Migration is selected.

Air_Migration_Roundtrip_Probability.description: Likelihood that an individual who flies to another cell will return to the cell of origin during the next migration. Relevant only when Enable_Air_Migration is selected.

Regional_Migration_Roundtrip_Probability.description: Likelihood that an individual who travels by vehicle to another cell will return to the cell of origin during the next migration. Relevant only when Enable_Regional_Migration is checked.

Sea_Migration_Roundtrip_Probability.description: Likelihood that an individual who travels by ship into a neighboring cell will return to the cell of origin during the next migration. Relevant only when Enable_Sea_Migration is checked.

Local_Migration_Roundtrip_Duration.description: The average time spent at the destination node during a round-trip migration by foot travel.

Air_Migration_Roundtrip_Duration.description: The average time spent at the destination node during a round-trip migration by airplane.

Regional_Migration_Roundtrip_Duration.description: The average time spent at the destination node during a round-trip migration by road network.

Sea_Migration_Roundtrip_Duration.description: The average time spent at the destination node during a round-trip migration by ship.

Roundtrip_Waypoints.description: The maximum number of points reached during a trip before steps are retraced on the return trip home.

Sexual_Debut_Age_Male_Weibull_Heterogene.description: Inverse shape of Weibull for male debut age.

Sexual_Debut_Age_Male_Weibull_Scale.description: Scale of Weibull for male debut age.

Sexual_Debut_Age_Female_Weibull_Heteroge.description: Inverse shape of Weibull for female debut age.

Sexual_Debut_Age_Female_Weibull_Scale.description: Scale of Weibull for female debut age.

STI_Coinfection_Multiplier.description: Per-act transmission probability multiplier for individuals with the coinfection flag.

Min_Days_Between_Adding_Relationships.description: Minimum number of days between adding two consecutive relationships as a means to control concurrency.  The constraint does not apply if an individual breaks an existing relationship.

Male_To_Female_Relative_Infectivity_Ages.description: Vector of ages governing the susceptibility of females relative to males, by age.

Male_To_Female_Relative_Infectivity_Mult.description: Vector of multiplicative factors governing the susceptibility of females relative to males, by age.  Multipliers are linearly interpolated between ages.  The left (right)-most value is used before (after) the first (last) age.

Condom_Transmission_Blocking_Probability.description: Per-act multiplier of the transmission probability when a condom is used.

Individual_Property_Name.description: Individual Property Key from demographics file or only one with value of NONE.

Extra_Relational_Flag_Type.description: Determines if extra-relational flags will be distributed in an independent or correlated way.  Possible values are INDEPENDENT and CORRELATED.

Prob_Extra_Transitory_Relationship_Male.description: Probability of a male receiving an extra-transitory flag.  The flag allows the individual to seek additional relationships while currently in a transitory relationship. Used for INDEPENDENT and CORRELATED values of STI_Extra_Relational_Flag_Type.

Prob_Extra_Transitory_Relationship_Femal.description: Probability of a female receiving an extra-transitory flag. The flag allows the individual to seek additional relationships while currently in a transitory relationship.  Used for INDEPENDENT and CORRELATED values of STI_Extra_Relational_Flag_Type.

Prob_Extra_Informal_Given_Extra_Transito.description: Probability of a male that received an extra-transitory flag also receiving an extra-informal flag. The flag allows the individual to seek additional relationships while currently in an informal relationship. Used only when STI_Extra_Relational_Flag_Type is CORRELATED.

Prob_Extra_Marital_Given_Extra_Informal_.description: Probability of a male that received an extra-informal flag also receiving an extra-marital flag. The flag allows the individual to seek additional relationships while currently in a marital relationship. Used only when STI_Extra_Relational_Flag_Type is CORRELATED.

Prob_Extra_Informal_Given_Extra_Transito.description: Probability of a female that received an extra-transitory flag also receiving an extra-informal flag. The flag allows the individual to seek additional relationships while currently in an informal relationship. Used only when STI_Extra_Relational_Flag_Type is CORRELATED.

Prob_Extra_Marital_Given_Extra_Informal_.description: Probability of a female that received an extra-informal flag also receiving an extra-marital flag. The flag allows the individual to seek additional relationships while currently in a marital relationship. Used only when STI_Extra_Relational_Flag_Type is CORRELATED.

Max_Simultaneous_Transitory_Relationship.description: Upper bound on the number of concurrent transitory relationships that a male is allowed to have.

Max_Simultaneous_Informal_Relationships_.description: Upper bound on the number of concurrent informal relationships that a male is allowed to have.

Max_Simultaneous_Marital_Relationships_M.description: Upper bound on the number of concurrent marital relationships that a male is allowed to have.

Max_Simultaneous_Transitory_Relationship.description: Upper bound on the number of concurrent transitory relationships that a female is allowed to have.

Max_Simultaneous_Informal_Relationships_.description: Upper bound on the number of concurrent informal relationships that a female is allowed to have.

Max_Simultaneous_Marital_Relationships_F.description: Upper bound on the number of concurrent marital relationships that a female is allowed to have.

STI_Network_Params_By_Property.description: The STI networking parameters to use for an individual given the individual's particular Individual Properties.

Mortality_Time_Course.description: Determines whether disease deaths are calculated on every time step or once at the end of the disease duration. Possible values are: DAILY_MORTALITY and MORTALITY_AFTER_INFECTIOUS.

Incubation_Period_Distribution.description: Distribution of duration of incubation period. Can be fixed or exponentially distributed with an average duration from Base_Incubation_Period. Possible values are: FIXED_DURATION and EXPONENTIAL_DURATION.

Base_Incubation_Period.description: Average duration, in days, of the incubation period before infected individuals becomes infectious.

Incubation_Period_Min.description: The minimum length of the incubation period. Used when the Incubation_Period_Distribution is UNIFORM_DURATION.

Incubation_Period_Max.description: The maximum length of the incubation period. Used when Incubation_Period_Distribution is UNIFORM_DURATION.

Incubation_Period_Mean.description: The standard deviation used when Incubation_Period_Distribution is either GAUSSIAN_DURATION or POISSON_DURATION.

Incubation_Period_Std_Dev.description: The standard deviation incubation period. Used when the Incubation_Period_Distribution is GAUSSIAN_DURATION.

Infectious_Period_Distribution.description: Distribution of duration of infectious period. Can be fixed or exponentially distributed with an average duration from Base_Infectious_Period. Possible values are: FIXED_DURATION, EXPONENTIAL_DURATION.

Base_Infectious_Period.description: Average duration, in days, of the infectious period before the infection is cleared.

Infectious_Period_Min.description: The minimum length of the infectious period. Used when the Infectious_Period_Distribution is UNIFORM_DURATION.

Infectious_Period_Max.description: The maximum length of the infectious period. Used when Infectious_Period_Distribution is UNIFORM_DURATION.

Infectious_Period_Mean.description: The mean of the infectious period. Used when Infectious_Period_Distribution is either GAUSSIAN_DURATION or POISSON_DURATION.

Infectious_Period_Std_Dev.description: The standard deviation of the infectious period. Used when the Infectious_Period_Distribution is GAUSSIAN_DURATION.

Base_Infectivity.description: The Base_Infectivity parameter determines the base infectiousness of individuals before accounting for transmission-blocking effects of acquired immunity and/or campaign interventions. It has a slightly different meaning for each of the disease types. GENERIC_SIM: The average number of individuals per time step who will be exposed to infection by one infectious individual. In the case of super-infection, the infectiousness is summed over all infections. VECTOR_SIM: The probability of infecting a mosquito during a successful blood meal (modulated by the vector parameter Acquire_Modifier). For vector simulations, the sum infectiousness of an individual is not allowed to exceed 100%. MALARIA_SIM: This simple scale factor is not used. Instead, gametocyte abundances and cytokine-mediated infectiousness are modeled explicitly.

Base_Mortality.description: The base mortality of the infection before accounting for individual immune modification factors. Depending on the setting of Mortality_Time_Course, this is either the daily probability of the disease being fatal (DAILY_MORTALITY) or the probability of death at the end of the infection duration (MORTALITY_AFTER_INFECTIOUS).

Malaria_Model.description: The type of malaria model used in a simulation. Possible values are:  MALARIA_FIXED_DURATION, MALARIA_EXPONENTIAL_DURATION, MALARIA_REDUCEDSTATE_MODEL and  MALARIA_MECHANISTIC_MODEL.  Important: All malaria simulations should use MALARIA_MECHANISTIC_MODEL. The others are placeholder values.

Mean_Sporozoites_Per_Bite.description: Mean number of sporozoites per infectious mosquito bite.

Base_Sporozoite_Survival_Fraction.description: Fraction of sporozoites that survive to infect a hepatocyte in the absence of anti-CSP protection.

Antibody_CSP_Killing_Threshold.description: Threshold value on CSP antibody concentration for sporozoite killing.

Antibody_CSP_Killing_Inverse_Width.description: Inverse width of sigmoidal sporozoite killing function of CSP antibody concentration.

Malaria_Strain_Model.description: The generator that is used to construct the antigenic repertoire of a malaria infection. Possible values are: FALCIPARUM_NONRANDOM_STRAIN, FALCIPARUM_RANDOM50_STRAIN, FALCIPARUM_RANDOM_STRAIN and FALCIPARUM_STRAIN_GENERATOR.

Parasite_Switch_Type.description: Parasite switch type for erythrocyte surface antigens. Possible values are: CONSTANT_SWITCH_RATE_2VARS, RATE_PER_PARASITE_7VARS - this is the one that is best parameterized - and finally,  RATE_PER_PARASITE_5VARS_DECAYING.

Antibody_IRBC_Kill_Rate.description: Factor multiplied by antibody level to produce the rate of clearance of the infected red blood cell (IRBC) population.

Nonspecific_Antigenicity_Factor.description: Nonspecific antigenicity factor that adjusts antibody IRBC killrate to account for IRBCs caused by antibody responses to antigenically weak surface proteins.

MSP1_Merozoite_Kill_Fraction.description: Fraction of merozoites inhibited from invading new erythrocytes when MSP1-specific antibody level is 1.

Gametocyte_Stage_Survival_Rate.description: Rate of gametocyte survival from one development stage to the next in the absence of drugs or inflammatory immune response.

Base_Gametocyte_Fraction_Male.description: Fraction of gametocytes that are male.

Antigen_Switch_Rate.description: Antigenic switching rate per infected red blood cell per asexual cycle. See Parasite_Switch_Type for different switching patterns.

Merozoites_Per_Hepatocyte.description: Number of IRBCs caused by a single infected hepatocyte at the start of infection.

Merozoites_Per_Schizont.description: Number of merozoites released by a single infected schizont after each asexual cycle. The number of resulting IRBC's depends on the RBC availability and merozoite-specific immunity.

RBC_Destruction_Multiplier.description: Number of total RBCs destroyed per infected rupturing schizont.

Number_Of_Asexual_Cycles_Without_Gametoc.description: Number of asexual reproduction cycles that do not produce gametocytes. All later cycles will produce gametocytes according to Base_Gametocyte_Production_Rate.

Anemia_Mortality_Threshold.description: The threshold value on hemoglobin count in grams per deciliter (g/dL) at which 50% of individuals die per day.

Parasite_Mortality_Threshold.description: The parasite-density mortality threshold for a simulation.

Fever_Mortality_Threshold.description: The fever mortality threshold for a simulation in units of degrees Celsius above normal body temperature. Sets the midpoint in the sigmoidal response for mortality rate associated with fever.

Enable_Sexual_Combination.description: Set to 1 to enable sexual combination of male and female gametocytes. Set to 0 for transmission of each strain only. Note: This parameter is currently not in use.

Base_Gametocyte_Mosquito_Survival_Rate.description: Average fraction of gametocytes in blood meal that are successful in infecting mosquito in the absence of other modulating effects, such as fever.

Cytokine_Gametocyte_Inactivation.description: The strength of inflammatory response inactivation of gametocytes.

Anemia_Mortality_Inverse_Width.description: The inverse width relative to threshold value of severe disease turn-on around threshold for anemia.

Parasite_Mortality_Inverse_Width.description: The inverse width relative to threshold value of mortality turn-on around threshold for parasite density.

Fever_Mortality_Inverse_Width.description: The inverse width relative to threshold value of mortality turn-on around threshold for fever.

Anemia_Severe_Threshold.description: The severe disease threshold level for anemia. Threshold units are in grams per deciliter (g/dL).

Parasite_Severe_Threshold.description: The severe disease threshold level for parasite density.

Fever_Severe_Threshold.description: The severe disease threshold level for fever.

Anemia_Severe_Inverse_Width.description: The inverse width relative to threshold value of severe disease turn-on around threshold for anemia.

Parasite_Severe_Inverse_Width.description: The inverse width relative to threshold value of severe disease turn-on around threshold for parasite density.

Fever_Severe_Inverse_Width.description: The inverse width relative to threshold value of severe disease turn-on around threshold for fever.

Clinical_Fever_Threshold_Low.description: The fever threshold (in degrees Celsius above normal) to end a clinical incident.

Clinical_Fever_Threshold_High.description: The fever threshold (in degrees Celsius above normal) to start a clinical incident.

Min_Days_Between_Clinical_Incidents.description: The number of days with fever below the low threshold before a new incident can start when the high fever threshold is again exceeded.

Antibody_Memory_Level.description: Limiting level of antibody capacity that remains after a prolonged absence of a specific antigen. The antibody capacity decays to this level gradually after infection is cleared. The decay rate in antibody capacity is set so that hyperimmunity is lost within 4 months, and capacity continues to decay to this level. The antibody memory level is relevant for year-scale dynamics, but not for long dynamics (10-20 years).

Max_MSP1_Antibody_Growthrate.description: Maximum increase in MSP1 antibody capacity during each asexual cycle. The higher this value, the sooner early clearances are observed and the earlier the parasite density envelope decreases.

Antibody_Stimulation_C50.description: Concentration of an antigen, measured in IRBC/ul at which growth in antibody capacity against the antigen increases at half the maximum rate specified by Antibody_Capacity_Growth_Rate.

Antibody_Capacity_Growth_Rate.description: Maximum daily rate of specific antibody capacity increase. Antibody production begins at capacity of 0.3. Hyperimmunity results at 0.4. The actual growth rate will tend to be lower and is a function of antigen concentrations.

Min_Adapted_Response.description: Minimum level of antibody stimulation to novel antigen. The value sets the low-range asymptote for antibody capacity growth, which is calculated from Antibody_Capacity_Growth_Rate and antigen density, in the presence of any nonzero antigen level.

Nonspecific_Antibody_Growth_Rate_Factor.description: Factor that adjusts Antibody_Capacity_Growth_Rate for less immunogenic surface proteins called the minor epitopes.

Antibody_CSP_Decay_Days.description: Exponential decay time for CSP antibody concentration (in days).

Erythropoiesis_Anemia_Effect.description: Exponential rate of increased red-blood-cell production from reduced red-blood-cell availability.

Maternal_Antibodies_Type.description: Type of maternal antibody protection.  Possible values are: OFF, SIMPLE_WANING, CONSTANT_INITIAL_IMMUNITY (independent of acquired immunity in possible mothers).

Maternal_Antibody_Protection.description: Strength of protection from maternal antibodies as a multiple of full antibody killing effect.

Maternal_Antibody_Decay_Rate.description: Decay rate per day in protection from maternal antibodies.

Innate_Immune_Variation_Type.description: Type of individual innate immune variation.  Possible values are: NONE (homogeneous), PYROGENIC_THRESHOLD (parasite threshold resulting in cytokine production), PYROGENIC_THRESHOLD_VS_AGE (age-dependent threshold), CYTOKINE_KILLING (effectiveness of cytokines in killing infected red-blood cells).

Pyrogenic_Threshold.description: Level of bloodstream infection, measured in IRBC per microliter, at which stimulation of the innate inflammatory immune response is half its maximum value.

Fever_IRBC_Kill_Rate.description: Factor multiplied by fever level to produce a decay rate of infected red blood cell population due to inflammatory innate immune response.

Infectivity_Scale_Type.description: Alter infectivity by time or season.  Possible values are: CONSTANT_INFECTIVITY - No infectivity correction is applied.  FUNCTION_OF_TIME_AND_LATITUDE - Infectivity is corrected for approximate seasonal forcing.  The use of a seasonal infectivity correction is a proxy for the effects of varying climate.  From October through March, infectivity increases in the Northern Hemisphere and decreases in the Southern Hemisphere.  From April through September, the trend reverses.  Regions closer to the equator have reduced forcing compared to temperate regions.  This is not a substitute for the weather-driven vector dynamics of vector-borne and malaria simulations.  FUNCTION_OF_CLIMATE - Allows infectivity to be modulated by weather directly, for example, relative humidity in airborne simulations or rainfall in environmental simulations.  There is no default climate dependence enabled for generic simulations.  EXPONENTIAL_FUNCTION_OF_TIME - To facilitate certain burn-in scenarios, infectivity ramps up from zero at the beginning of the simulation according to the functional form, 1-exp(-rate*time), where the rate is specified by the parameter Infectivity_Scaling_Rate.

Infectivity_Sinusoidal_Forcing_Amplitude.description: Only used or needed when Infectivity_Scale_Type is set to SINUSOIDAL_FUNCTION_OF_TIME.  Sets the amplitude of sinusoidal variations in Base_Infectivity.

Infectivity_Sinusoidal_Forcing_Phase.description: Only used or needed when Infectivity_Scale_Type is set to SINUSOIDAL_FUNCTION_OF_TIME.  Sets the phase of sinusoidal variations in Base_Infectivity.

Infectivity_Boxcar_Forcing_Amplitude.description: Fractional increase in R0 during high infectivity season, when Infectivity_Scale_Type is equal to ANNUAL_BOXCAR_FUNCTION.

Infectivity_Boxcar_Forcing_Start_Time.description: Beginning of high infectivity season, when Infectivity_Scale_Type is equal to ANNUAL_BOXCAR_FUNCTION.

Infectivity_Boxcar_Forcing_End_Time.description: End of high infectivity season, when Infectivity_Scale_Type is equal to ANNUAL_BOXCAR_FUNCTION.

Animal_Reservoir_Type.description: Configures whether there is an animal reservoir and how the risk of zoonosis in configured. Use of the animal reservoir sets a low constant baseline of infectivity beyond what is present in the human population. It allows a more random introduction of cases in continuous time, which is more applicable for various situations such as zoonosis. Possible values are: NO_ZOONOSIS, CONSTANT_ZOONOSIS where the daily rate of zoonotic infection is configured by the parameter Zoonosis_Rate, and ZOONOSIS_FROM_DEMOGRAPHICS where the zoonosis rate is additionally scaled by the node-specific Zoonosis value in the NodeAttributes section of a demographics overlay file.  See Zoonosis_Rate.

Zoonosis_Rate.description: The daily rate of zoonotic infection per individual when the Animal_Reservoir_Type parameter is set to either CONSTANT_ZOONOSIS or ZOONOSIS_FROM_DEMOGRAPHICS.

Enable_Demographics_Birth.description: Assumes that newborn characteristics such as sickle-cell status are heterogeneous. Set to 0 to assume by default that all newborns have identical characteristics.

Enable_Demographics_Other.description: Includes the impact of other relevant demographic factors. For example, fraction of individuals above poverty, urban/rural characteristics, heterogeneous initial immunity and risk. Set to 0 to run the simulation without other relevant demographic factors.

Enable_Demographics_Gender.description: Enable_Demographics_Gender=0 assigns gender based on a 50/50 draw, while Enable_Demographics_Gender=1 draws from a male/female ratio that is randomly smeared by a Gaussian of width 1%.

Enable_Maternal_Transmission.description: Set to 1 to account for infection of infants at birth by infected mothers. Set to 0 to assume that infection is not transmitted by mothers to infants at birth.

Enable_Birth.description: Set to 1 to enable individuals to be added to the simulation by birth.

Birth_Rate_Dependence.description: This parameter determines how the birth rate specified in the demographics file is used. Possible values are: FIXED_BIRTH_RATE- The absolute rate at which new individuals are born. POPULATION_DEP_RATE - Scales the node population to determine the birth rate. DEMOGRAPHIC_DEP_RATE - Scales the female population within fertility age ranges to determine the birth rate. INDIVIDUAL_PREGNANCIES - Results in a similar birth rate as DEMOGRAPHIC_DEP_RATE, but pregnancies are assigned on an individual basis and result in a 40-week pregnancy for a specific individual with a birth at the end, INDIVIDUAL_PREGNANCIES_BY_URBAN_AND_AGE, and INDIVIDUAL_PREGNANCIES_BY_AGE_AND_YEAR

Individual_Sampling_Type.description: Type of individual human sampling. Possible values are: TRACK_ALL, FIXED_SAMPLING, ADAPTED_SAMPLING_BY_POPULATION_SIZE, ADAPTED_SAMPLING_BY_AGE_GROUP, and ADAPTED_SAMPLING_BY_AGE_GROUP_AND_POP_SIZE.

Base_Population_Scale_Factor.description: If Population_Scale_Type is set to FIXED_SCALING, the initial simulation population is uniformly scaled over the entire area to adjust for historical or future population density.

Max_Node_Population_Samples.description: Number of individuals when the sampling rate starts dropping to the rate of adapted sampling by population size.

Population_Density_Infectivity_Correctio.description: Correction to alter infectivity by population density set in the Population_Density_C50 parameter. Measured in people per sq. km. Possible values are:  CONSTANT_INFECTIVITY and SATURATING_FUNCTION_OF_DENSITY.   Note: Sparsely populated areas have a lower infectivity, while densely populated areas have a higher infectivity which rises to saturate at the Base_Infectivity value.

x_Birth.description: Multiplier of birth rate from input demographics file.

Birth_Rate_Time_Dependence.description: Allows for time dependence in the birth rate.  Available values are NONE, SINUSOIDAL_FUNCTION_OF_TIME, ANNUAL_BOXCAR_FUNCTION

Birth_Rate_Sinusoidal_Forcing_Amplitude.description: Only used or needed when Birth_Rate_Time_Dependence is equal to SINUSOIDAL_FUNCTION_OF_TIME.  Sets the amplitude of sinusoidal variations in birth rate.

Birth_Rate_Sinusoidal_Forcing_Phase.description: Only used or needed when Birth_Rate_Time_Dependence is equal to SINUSOIDAL_FUNCTION_OF_TIME.  Sets the phase of sinusoidal variations in birth rate.

Birth_Rate_Boxcar_Forcing_Amplitude.description: Fractional increase in birth rate during high birth season, when Birth_Rate_Time_Dependence is equal to ANNUAL_BOXCAR_FUNCTION.

Birth_Rate_Boxcar_Forcing_Start_Time.description: Beginning of high birth rate season, when Birth_Rate_Time_Dependence is equal to ANNUAL_BOXCAR_FUNCTION.

Birth_Rate_Boxcar_Forcing_End_Time.description: End of high birth rate season, when Birth_Rate_Time_Dependence is equal to ANNUAL_BOXCAR_FUNCTION.

Infection_Updates_Per_Timestep.description: Number of infection updates executed during each timestep. A timestep defaults to one day.

Enable_Immunity.description: Set to 1 if an individual has protective immunity after an infection clears. Set to 0 if recovery from the infection does not affect the individual's future immunity.

Max_Individual_Infections.description: Limit on the number of infections that an individual can have simultaneously. Note: Relevant only if the Enable_Superinfection parameter is set to 1 to allow multiple infections.

Enable_Superinfection.description: Set to 1 if an individual can have multiple infections with the same agent simultaneously. Set to 0 if multiple infections are not possible. See the Max_Individual_Infections parameter.

x_Other_Mortality.description: Multiplier for scaling mortality from causes other than disease being simulated.

Migration_Model.description: Model to use for migration. Possible values are: NO_MIGRATION, FIXED_RATE_MIGRATION, VARIABLE_RATE_MIGRATION and  LEVY_FLIGHTS.  Note: VARIABLE_RATE_MIGRATION and LEVY FLIGHTS are currently not supported.

Extra_Relational_Rate_Ratio_Male.description: The ratio of relationship formation rates, for a particular relationship type, between individuals having an extra-relational flag (numerator) and those without a flag (denominator). This parameter applies to males.

PFA_Cum_Prob_Selection_Threshold.description: This parameter serves to minimize the extent to which relationships with unlikely age gaps are formed. These unlikely relationships could be generated due to lack of diversity in the PFA. Within the algorithm, males pick from amongst the available females by age bin, weighted by the conditional of the joint_probability matrix given the male age bin.  If the sum of the probabilities in the female age bins that are not empty is below this threshold, the male will wait till the next update. Setting this parameter to a value near 1 dramatically increases the delay that individuals well experience in seeking relationships. Setting this parameter to 0 disables the feature.

Enable_Immune_Decay.description: Set to 1 if immunity decays after an infection clears. Set to 0 if recovery from the disease confers complete immunity for life.

Acquisition_Blocking_Immunity_Decay_Rate.description: Rate at which acquisition-blocking immunity decays after the initial period indicated by the base acquisition-blocking immunity offset. Relevant only when Enable_Immunity and Enable_Immune_Decay parameters are set to 1.

Transmission_Blocking_Immunity_Decay_Rat.description: Rate at which transmission-blocking immunity decays after the base transmission-blocking immunity offset period. Relevant only when Enable_Immunity and Enable_Immune_Decay parameters are set to 1.

Mortality_Blocking_Immunity_Decay_Rate.description: Rate at which mortality-blocking immunity decays after the mortality-blocking immunity offset period. Relevant only when Enable_Immunity and Enable_Immune_Decay parameters are set to 1.

Immunity_Acquisition_Factor.description: Multiplicative reduction in probability of reacquiring the disease. Relevant only when Enable_Immunity and Enable_Immune_Decay parameters are set to 1.

Immunity_Transmission_Factor.description: Multiplicative reduction in probability of transmitting infection after getting re-infected. Relevant only when Enable_Immunity and Enable_Immune_Decay parameters are set to 1.

Immunity_Mortality_Factor.description: Multiplicative reduction in probability of dying from infection after getting re-infected. Relevant only when Enable_Immunity and Enable_Immune_Decay parameters are set to 1.

Acquisition_Blocking_Immunity_Duration_B.description: Number of days after infection until acquisition-blocking immunity begins to decay. Relevant only when Enable_Immunity and Enable_Immune_Decay parameters are set to 1.

Transmission_Blocking_Immunity_Duration_.description: Number of days after infection until transmission-blocking immunity begins to decay. Relevant only when Enable_Immunity and Enable_Immune_Decay parameters are set to 1.

Mortality_Blocking_Immunity_Duration_Bef.description: Number of days after infection until mortality-blocking immunity begins to decay. Relevant only when Enable_Immunity and Enable_Immune_Decay parameters are set to 1.

TB_Immune_Loss_Fraction.description: Fraction of individuals that lose immunity with time.

TB_Fast_Progressor_Fraction_Child.description: Fraction of children (under age 15) that are fast-progressors.

TB_Fast_Progressor_Fraction_Adult.description: Fraction of adults (age 15 or over) that are fast-progressors.

TB_Smear_Positive_Fraction_Child.description: Fraction of active cases in children (under age 15) that are smear-positive. The sum of TB_Smear_Positive_Fraction_Child and TB_Extrapulmonary_Fraction_Child must be less than or equal to 1. The fraction of smear-negative children is 1 - ( TB_Smear_Positive_Fraction_Child + TB_Extrapulmonary_Fraction_Child ).

TB_Smear_Positive_Fraction_Adult.description: Fraction of active cases in adults (age 15 and over) that are smear-positive. The sum of TB_Smear_Positive_Fraction_Adult and TB_Extrapulmonary_Fraction_Adult must be less than or equal to 1. The fraction of smear-negative adults is 1 - ( TB_Smear_Positive_Fraction_Adult + TB_Extrapulmonary_Fraction_Adult ).

TB_Extrapulmonary_Fraction_Child.description: Fraction of active cases in children (under age 15) that are extrapulmonary. The sum of TB_Smear_Positive_Fraction_Child and TB_Extrapulmonary_Fraction_Child must be less than or equal to 1.

TB_Extrapulmonary_Fraction_Adult.description: Fraction of active cases in adults (age 15 or over) that are extrapulmonary. The sum of TB_Smear_Positive_Fraction_Adult and TB_Extrapulmonary_Fraction_Adult must be less than or equal to 1.

TB_Latent_Cure_Rate.description: The mean rate at which individuals progress from a latently infected state to a cured (uninfected) state. This rate is added to either the TB_Fast_Progressor_Rate or the TB_Slow_Progressor_Rate to determine total_rate of the latently infected state (depending on whether the individual is a fast-progressor or slow-progressor, respectively), then the ratio of TB_Latent_Cure_Rate to total_rate is calculated. This ratio determines the probability that a latently infected individual will go to a cured state after a mean duration of 1 / total_rate.

TB_Fast_Progressor_Rate.description: The mean rate at which individuals who are fast-progressors progress from a latently infected state to an active presymptomatic state. This rate is added to the TB_Latent_Cure_Rate to determine total_rate of the latently infected state, then the ratio of TB_Fast_Progressor_Rate to the total_rate is calculated. This ratio determines the probability that a latently infected fast-progressor will go to an active presymptomatic state after a mean duration of 1 / total_rate.

TB_Slow_Progressor_Rate.description: The mean rate at which individuals who are slow-progressors progress from a latently infected state to an active presymptomatic state. This rate is added to the TB_Latent_Cure_Rate to determine total_rate of the latently infected state, then the ratio of TB_Slow_Progressor_Rate to the total_rate is calculated. This ratio determines the probability that a latently infected fast-progressor will go to an active presymptomatic state after a mean duration of 1 / total_rate.

TB_Active_Cure_Rate.description: The mean rate at which active symptomatic individuals progress to a cured (uninfected) state. In the absence of treatment, this rate is added to TB_Inactivation_Rate and TB_Active_Mortality_Rate to determine the total_rate of the active smear-positive state, then the ratio of TB_Active_Cure_Rate to total_rate determines the probability that an actively infected individual will go to a cured state after a mean duration of 1 / total_rate.

TB_Inactivation_Rate.description: The mean rate at which active symptomatic (smear-positive, smear-negative, and extrapulmonary) individuals progress to an inactivated (latently infected) state. In the absence of treatment, this rate is added to TB_Active_Cure_Rate and TB_Active_Mortality_Rate to determine the total_rate of the active symptomatic state, then the ratio of TB_Active_Cure_Rate to total_rate determines the probability that an active syptomatic individual will go to a latently infected state after a mean duration of 1 / total_rate.

TB_Active_Mortality_Rate.description: The mean rate at which active smear-positive individuals die from TB disease. In the absence of treatment, this rate is added to TB_Active_Cure_Rate and TB_Inactivation_Rate to determine the total_rate of the active smear-positive state, then the ratio of TB_Active_Mortality_Rate to total_rate determines the probability that an active smear-positive individual will die from TB disease after a mean duration of 1 / total_rate.

TB_Extrapulmonary_Mortality_Multiplier.description: A constant by which TB_Active_Mortality_Rate is multiplied to give the mortality rate of active extrapulmonary individuals. In the absence of treatment, the product is added to TB_Active_Cure_Rate and TB_Inactivation_Rate to determine the total_rate of the active extrapulmonary state, then the ratio of the aforementioned product to total_rate determines the probability that an active extrapulmonary individual will die from TB disease after mean duration of 1 / total_rate.

TB_Smear_Negative_Mortality_Multiplier.description: A constant by which TB_Active_Mortality_Rate is multiplied to give the mortality rate of active smear-negative individuals. In the absence of treatment, the product is added to TB_Active_Cure_Rate and TB_Inactivation_Rate to determine the total_rate of the active smear-negative state, then the ratio of the aforementioned product to total_rate determines the probability that an active smear-negative individual will die from TB disease after mean duration of 1 / total_rate.

TB_Active_Presymptomatic_Infectivity_Mul.description: A constant by which Base_Infectivity is multiplied to give the infectiousness of active presymptomatic individuals.

TB_Presymptomatic_Rate.description: The mean rate at which active presymptomatic individuals progress to an active symptomatic state. This rate is added to TB_Presymptomatic_Cure_Rate to determine total_rate of the active presymptomatic state, then the ratio of TB_Presymptomatic_Rate to total_rate is calculated. This ratio determines the probability that an active presymptomatic individual will go to active symptomatic disease after a mean duration of 1 / total_rate.

TB_Presymptomatic_Cure_Rate.description: The mean rate at which active presymptomatic individuals progress to a cured (uninfected) state. This rate is added to TB_Presymptomatic_Rate to determine total_rate of the active presymptomatic state, then the ratio of TB_Presymptomatic_Cure_Rate to total_rate is calculated. This ratio determines the probability that an active presymptomatic individual will go to a cured state after a mean duration of 1 / total_rate.

TB_Smear_Negative_Infectivity_Multiplier.description: A constant by which Base_Infectivity is multiplied to give the infectiousness of active smear-negative individuals.

TB_Drug_Efficacy_Multiplier_MDR.description: A constant by which drug efficacy parameters (TB_Drug_Inactivation_Rate and TB_Drug_Clearance_Rate) are multiplied to give the efficacy of first-line drugs when given to individuals with MDR-TB. The value of 1 assumes equal efficacy for drug-sensitive TB and MDR-TB.

TB_Drug_Efficacy_Multiplier_Failed.description: A constant by which drug efficacy parameters (TB_Drug_Inactivation_Rate and TB_Drug_Clearance_Rate) are multiplied to give the efficacy of first-line drugs when given to individuals who have failed treatment. The value of 1 assumes equal efficacy for treatment-naive and treatment-failed individuals.

TB_Drug_Efficacy_Multiplier_Relapsed.description: A constant by which drug efficacy parameters (TB_Drug_Inactivation_Rate and TB_Drug_Clearance_Rate) are multiplied to give the efficacy of first-line drugs when given to individuals who have relapsed after treatment. The value of 1 assumes equal efficacy for treatment-naive and relapsed individuals.

TB_MDR_Fitness_Multiplier.description: A constant by which Base_Infectivity is multipled 1 to give the infectiousness of MDR-TB strains. The value of 1 assumes equal infectiousness of drug-sensitive TB and MDR-TB.

TB_Relapsed_to_Active_Rate.description: The mean rate at which relapsed individuals progress to an active symptomatic state. By default, the same value as the TB_Fast_Progressor_Rate is used.

TB_Active_Period_Distribution.description: Distribution for duration of active disease. For both EXPONENTIAL_DURATION and GAUSSIAN_DURATION, the mean is defined by total_rate which is the sum of TB_Inactivation_Rate and TB_Active_Mortality_Rate corrected for smear status. For GAUSSIAN_DURATION, an additional parameter TB_Active_Period_Std_Dev is used to provide a value for standard deviation.

TB_Active_Period_Std_Dev.description: When TB_Active_Period_Distribution is set to GAUSSIAN_DURATION, this parameter provides the value for standard deviation.

Age_Dependent_Biting_Risk_Type.description: Type of functional form for age-dependent biting-risk.  Possible values are: OFF, LINEAR, SURFACE_AREA_DEPENDENT.

Newborn_Biting_Risk_Multiplier.description: For age-dependent biting risk type = linear; defines the y-intercept of the linear portion of the biting risk curve.

If EXPONENTIAL_DURATION is specified as the Delay_Distribution, Delay_Period, represents the exponential rate that describes the distribution of the time delay (in units of 1/days).

Delay_Period_Min.description: If a UNIFORM_DURATION is specified as the Delay_Distribution, add this parameter Delay_Period_Min to directly specify the minimum time delay (in number of days).

Delay_Period_Max.description: If a UNIFORM_DURATION is specified as the Delay_Distribution, add this parameter Delay_Period_Max to directly specify the maximum time delay (in number of days).

Delay_Period_Mean.description: If a GAUSSIAN_DURATION is specified as the Delay_Distribution, add this parameter Delay_Period_Mean to directly specify the mean time delay (in number of days).

Delay_Period_Std_Dev.description: If a GAUSSIAN_DURATION is specified as the Delay_Distribution, add this parameter Delay_Period_Std_Dev to specify the standard deviation describing the Gaussian distribution (in number of days).

Values.description: An array of values to match the defined Times.

Time_Varying_Constants.description: For PIECEWISE_CONSTANT and PIECEWISE_LINEAR delay distributions, this structure maps simulation year to a delay period.

Broadcast_Event.description: The event that should occur at the end of the delay period.

Broadcast_On_Expiration_Event.description: If the delay intervention expires before arriving at the end of the delay period, this specifies the event that should occur. For example, if loss to follow-up occurs at a high rate for the first 6 months of care, and then later transitions to a lower rate, then the Expiration_Period should be set to 183 days and Broadcast_On_Expiration_Event can link to another delay intervention with a longer average delay time until LTFU. If LTFU does not occur in the first 6 months, then the expiration will allow the first rate to give way to the post-6-month rate.

Interpolation_Order.description: When set to zero, interpolation between values in the Time_Value_Map is zero-order ('staircase'). When set to 1, interpolation between values in the Time_Value_Map is linear. The final value is held constant for all times after the last time specified in the Time_Value_Map.

Female_Multiplier.description: Allows for the probabilities in the Time_Value_Map to be different for males and females, by multiplying the female probabilities by a constant value.

Default_Value.description: The probability of positive 'diagnosis' if the intervention is used before the earliest specified time in the Time_Value_Map.

Values.description: An array of values to match the defined Times.

Time_Value_Map.description: A JSON structure containing one array of Times and one for Values, which allows for a time-variable probability that can take on any shape over time. When queried at a simulation year corresponding to one of the listed Times, it returns the corresponding Value. When queried earlier than the first listed Time, it returns the Default value. When queried in between listed Times, it either returns the value for the most recent past time (when Interpolation_Order is 0) or linearly interpolates Values between Times (when Interpolation_Order is 1). When queried after the last Time in the list, it returns the last Value. The Times and Values must be of equal length, and can consist of a single value. Times must monotonically increase.
